imagine we are reviewing stage area, and we find some changes
that we add, but we don't want it!
we want to UNDO the add command and restore changes.

for this we use "RESTORE" command.      git restore --staged fileName
                                        git restore --staged fileName1 fileName2
                                        git restore --staged .          //period restore all files
                                                                        //“.” has traditionally marked the end of a period of speech or thought
                                                                        //so we call it period

Note: the command is "restore"
      because it restore the file from pre "commit"
      so after restoring, we have the pre commit stage


